    -- LESSON 16: Debugging AI Systems
    UPDATE lessons SET content = '<div class="lesson-content"><h2>Debugging AI Systems</h2><h3>When Things Go Wrong</h3><p>Even with AI assistance, code breaks, features don''t work as expected, and bugs appear. Debugging AI-generated code requires a slightly different approach than debugging code you wrote yourself. This lesson teaches you how to effectively debug AI systems and fix issues quickly.</p><h3>Why AI-Generated Code Breaks</h3><p>Common reasons for bugs in AI code: Misunderstood requirements (AI interpreted your prompt differently than intended). Missing edge cases (AI didn''t consider unusual scenarios). Integration issues (AI-generated code doesn''t fit with existing code). Outdated patterns (AI used deprecated methods or libraries). Logical errors (AI''s reasoning was flawed). Context limitations (AI didn''t have full picture of your system).</p><h3>The AI Debugging Mindset</h3><p>Debugging with AI is different: You didn''t write the code, so you need to understand it first. AI can help debug its own code. You can ask AI to explain what went wrong. The bug might be in your prompt, not the code.</p><h3>Step-by-Step Debugging Process</h3><h4>Step 1: Reproduce the Issue</h4><p>Confirm the bug exists: What exactly is broken? When does it happen? What are the steps to reproduce? What''s the expected vs actual behavior?</p><h4>Step 2: Understand the Code</h4><p>Before fixing, understand what the code does: Ask AI: "Explain what this function does step by step." Read through the logic. Identify the relevant parts.</p><h4>Step 3: Isolate the Problem</h4><p>Narrow down where the bug is: Is it frontend or backend? Which function or component? What data is involved? Add console.logs or breakpoints.</p><h4>Step 4: Diagnose the Cause</h4><p>Ask AI for help: "This function is supposed to [expected behavior] but instead it [actual behavior]. Why might this be happening?"</p><h4>Step 5: Implement the Fix</h4><p>Once you understand the cause: "Fix this bug: [describe the issue and cause]." Review the proposed fix. Test thoroughly.</p><h4>Step 6: Prevent Recurrence</h4><p>Add safeguards: "Add validation to prevent this issue in the future." "Add error handling for this edge case." "Write a test that would have caught this bug."</p><h3>Common AI Code Bugs and Fixes</h3><h4>Bug 1: Null/Undefined Errors</h4><p>Symptom: "Cannot read property of undefined"<br>Cause: AI didn''t check if data exists before using it.<br>Fix: "Add null checks before accessing [property]. Use optional chaining (?.) where appropriate."</p><h4>Bug 2: Infinite Loops or Re-renders</h4><p>Symptom: Page freezes, browser becomes unresponsive.<br>Cause: Missing dependencies in useEffect, incorrect loop conditions.<br>Fix: "This component is re-rendering infinitely. Add proper dependencies to useEffect and add exit conditions to loops."</p><h4>Bug 3: Async/Await Issues</h4><p>Symptom: Data not loading, promises not resolving.<br>Cause: Missing await keywords, improper promise handling.<br>Fix: "This async function isn''t waiting for data. Add await to all async operations and handle errors properly."</p><h4>Bug 4: State Management Problems</h4><p>Symptom: UI not updating, stale data displayed.<br>Cause: Direct state mutation, incorrect state updates.<br>Fix: "State isn''t updating correctly. Use functional updates and avoid mutating state directly."</p><h4>Bug 5: API Errors</h4><p>Symptom: 400/500 errors, failed requests.<br>Cause: Incorrect endpoints, missing headers, bad data format.<br>Fix: "API calls are failing with [error]. Check the endpoint URL, request headers, and data format."</p><h3>Using AI as Your Debugging Partner</h3><h4>Technique 1: Explain the Symptoms</h4><p>"When I click the submit button, nothing happens. The console shows no errors. The form has name and email fields. What could be wrong?"</p><h4>Technique 2: Share Error Messages</h4><p>"I''m getting this error: [paste full error message]. Here''s the relevant code: [paste code]. What''s causing this and how do I fix it?"</p><h4>Technique 3: Describe Expected vs Actual</h4><p>"This function should return the sum of all numbers in the array, but it''s returning NaN. Here''s the function: [paste code]. What''s wrong?"</p><h4>Technique 4: Ask for Step-by-Step Analysis</h4><p>"Walk me through what this code does line by line, and identify where the bug might be."</p><h3>Advanced Debugging Techniques</h3><h4>Console Logging Strategy</h4><p>Ask AI to add strategic logs: "Add console.logs to track: Input values at function start. Intermediate calculations. API request/response. Final return value."</p><h4>Breakpoint Debugging</h4><p>"Where should I set breakpoints to debug this issue? What variables should I inspect at each breakpoint?"</p><h4>Network Debugging</h4><p>"The API call isn''t working. Help me debug by checking: Request URL and method. Request headers and body. Response status and data. CORS settings."</p><h4>State Debugging</h4><p>"Add logging to track state changes in this component. Show: Initial state. What triggers updates. New state after each update."</p><h3>Debugging Different Layers</h3><h4>Frontend Debugging</h4><p>UI not displaying correctly: "Inspect the component tree and identify which component isn''t rendering. Check props being passed." Events not firing: "Add event listeners logging to confirm events are triggering. Check event handler bindings."</p><h4>Backend Debugging</h4><p>API endpoints failing: "Test the endpoint with curl/Postman. Check server logs for errors. Verify database connections." Database queries not working: "Log the actual SQL being executed. Check for syntax errors. Verify table/column names."</p><h4>Integration Debugging</h4><p>Frontend and backend not communicating: "Check CORS settings. Verify API URLs match. Confirm request/response formats. Check authentication headers."</p><h3>Preventing Bugs with AI</h3><h4>Request Defensive Code</h4><p>"Write this function with: Input validation. Error handling. Null checks. Type checking (if using TypeScript)."</p><h4>Ask for Edge Case Handling</h4><p>"What edge cases should this function handle? Add code to handle: Empty inputs. Invalid data types. Extreme values. Network failures."</p><h4>Generate Tests</h4><p>"Write tests for this function covering: Normal cases. Edge cases. Error conditions. Boundary values."</p><h3>When AI Can''t Fix the Bug</h3><p>Sometimes AI struggles with complex bugs: The bug requires deep domain knowledge. The issue is in external dependencies. The problem is environmental (not in code). The bug is intermittent and hard to reproduce.</p><p>In these cases: Break the problem down smaller. Provide more context about your system. Try a different AI tool. Search for similar issues online. Ask in developer communities.</p><h3>Debugging Checklist</h3><p>Before asking AI for help: ‚òê Can you reproduce the bug consistently? ‚òê Do you have the full error message? ‚òê Have you identified which part of the code is involved? ‚òê Do you understand what the code is supposed to do? ‚òê Have you checked for typos and simple mistakes? ‚òê Have you reviewed recent changes?</p><h3>Common Debugging Mistakes</h3><p><strong>Mistake 1: Fixing Symptoms, Not Causes</strong><br>Don''t just make the error go away‚Äîunderstand why it happened.</p><p><strong>Mistake 2: Making Multiple Changes at Once</strong><br>Change one thing at a time so you know what fixed it.</p><p><strong>Mistake 3: Not Testing the Fix</strong><br>Always verify the fix works and doesn''t break anything else.</p><p><strong>Mistake 4: Not Learning from Bugs</strong><br>Understand the root cause to avoid similar bugs in the future.</p><h3>Key Takeaways</h3><ul><li>AI-generated code breaks for <strong>specific reasons</strong>: misunderstood requirements, missing edge cases, integration issues</li><li>Follow a <strong>systematic debugging process</strong>: reproduce, understand, isolate, diagnose, fix, prevent</li><li>Use AI as your <strong>debugging partner</strong> by explaining symptoms and sharing errors</li><li>Add <strong>defensive code</strong> to prevent bugs: validation, error handling, null checks</li><li><strong>Test thoroughly</strong> after fixes to ensure nothing else broke</li><li>Learn from each bug to <strong>improve your prompts</strong> and prevent similar issues</li></ul><p>In the next lesson, we''ll apply everything you''ve learned to build a complete SaaS application with AI.</p></div>'
