    -- LESSON 17: Building a SaaS with AI
    UPDATE lessons SET content = '<div class="lesson-content"><h2>Building a SaaS with AI</h2><h3>From Idea to Launch</h3><p>Building a Software-as-a-Service (SaaS) product used to require months of development and a team of engineers. With Vibe Coding, you can build and launch a SaaS in days or weeks. This lesson walks you through the complete process of building a real SaaS application using AI tools.</p><h3>What We''re Building</h3><p>For this lesson, we''ll build "TaskFlow" - a simple project management SaaS with: User authentication and accounts. Project creation and management. Task boards with drag-and-drop. Team collaboration. Subscription billing. Admin dashboard.</p><h3>Phase 1: Planning and Design</h3><h4>Define Your Core Value Proposition</h4><p>"TaskFlow helps small teams manage projects without complexity. Unlike bloated tools, we focus on simplicity and speed."</p><h4>Identify Core Features (MVP)</h4><p>Must-have for launch: User signup/login. Create projects. Add tasks to projects. Assign tasks to team members. Mark tasks complete. Basic subscription (free/paid tiers).</p><p>Nice-to-have (post-launch): File attachments. Comments on tasks. Time tracking. Advanced analytics.</p><h4>Design the User Flow</h4><p>Map out the user journey: Landing page ‚Üí Signup ‚Üí Onboarding ‚Üí Dashboard ‚Üí Create project ‚Üí Add tasks ‚Üí Invite team ‚Üí Manage subscription.</p><h4>Choose Your Tech Stack</h4><p>For TaskFlow, we''ll use: Frontend: Next.js 14 with TypeScript. Styling: Tailwind CSS. Backend: Supabase (database, auth, storage). Payments: Stripe. Deployment: Vercel. AI Tools: v0 for components, Cursor for development, ChatGPT for logic.</p><h3>Phase 2: Setting Up the Foundation</h3><h4>Step 1: Initialize the Project</h4><p>Prompt to v0 or Cursor: "Create a Next.js 14 project with TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, and ESLint. Set up the basic folder structure: app/, components/, lib/, types/."</p><h4>Step 2: Set Up Supabase</h4><p>Prompt: "Help me set up Supabase for this project. I need: Database tables for users, projects, tasks, team_members. Authentication with email/password and Google OAuth. Row-level security policies. Supabase client configuration for Next.js."</p><h4>Step 3: Create the Database Schema</h4><p>Prompt: "Create Supabase tables: users (id, email, name, avatar_url, subscription_tier, created_at). projects (id, name, description, owner_id, created_at). tasks (id, project_id, title, description, status, assigned_to, due_date, created_at). team_members (id, project_id, user_id, role, joined_at). Include proper foreign keys and indexes."</p><h3>Phase 3: Building Core Features</h3><h4>Feature 1: Authentication</h4><p>Prompt: "Build authentication system: Signup page with email/password. Login page with email/password and Google OAuth. Password reset flow. Protected routes (redirect to login if not authenticated). User session management. Logout functionality."</p><h4>Feature 2: Dashboard</h4><p>Prompt: "Create a dashboard that shows: List of user''s projects (cards with name, task count, team size). ''Create New Project'' button. Recent activity feed. User profile dropdown in header. Clean, modern design similar to Linear."</p><h4>Feature 3: Project Management</h4><p>Prompt: "Build project features: Create project modal (name, description). Project detail page showing all tasks. Edit/delete project (owner only). Invite team members by email. Project settings page."</p><h4>Feature 4: Task Management</h4><p>Prompt: "Implement task functionality: Create task form (title, description, assignee, due date). Task list with status columns (To Do, In Progress, Done). Drag-and-drop to change status. Edit task modal. Delete task with confirmation. Filter tasks by assignee or status."</p><h3>Phase 4: Adding Polish</h3><h4>Loading States</h4><p>Prompt: "Add loading states throughout the app: Skeleton loaders for dashboard. Spinner for form submissions. Loading indicator for data fetching. Optimistic updates where appropriate."</p><h4>Error Handling</h4><p>Prompt: "Implement comprehensive error handling: Toast notifications for errors. Graceful error messages (user-friendly, not technical). Retry logic for failed API calls. Error boundaries for React components. 404 and error pages."</p><h4>Responsive Design</h4><p>Prompt: "Make the entire app responsive: Mobile-first approach. Hamburger menu on mobile. Touch-friendly buttons and interactions. Responsive grid layouts. Test on 320px to 1920px widths."</p><h3>Phase 5: Subscription and Billing</h3><h4>Set Up Stripe</h4><p>Prompt: "Integrate Stripe for subscriptions: Create Stripe products (Free, Pro $10/month, Team $25/month). Implement checkout flow. Handle successful payments. Manage subscription status in database. Create customer portal for managing subscriptions. Webhook handlers for Stripe events."</p><h4>Feature Gating</h4><p>Prompt: "Implement subscription tiers: Free: 2 projects, 10 tasks per project. Pro: Unlimited projects, 100 tasks per project. Team: Unlimited everything plus team features. Check tier before allowing actions. Show upgrade prompts when limits reached."</p><h3>Phase 6: Testing and Quality Assurance</h3><h4>Functional Testing</h4><p>Test every feature: Can users sign up and log in? Can they create projects and tasks? Does drag-and-drop work? Do permissions work correctly? Does billing flow work end-to-end?</p><h4>Edge Case Testing</h4><p>Prompt: "Help me test edge cases: What happens with empty inputs? How do we handle very long project names? What if a user deletes a project with tasks? What if payment fails? What if database is slow to respond?"</p><h4>Performance Testing</h4><p>Prompt: "Optimize performance: Implement pagination for large task lists. Add database indexes for common queries. Lazy load images and heavy components. Minimize bundle size. Add caching where appropriate."</p><h3>Phase 7: Deployment</h3><h4>Deploy to Vercel</h4><p>Prompt: "Help me deploy to Vercel: Set up environment variables. Configure build settings. Set up custom domain. Enable automatic deployments from GitHub. Set up preview deployments for PRs."</p><h4>Set Up Monitoring</h4><p>Prompt: "Add monitoring and analytics: Error tracking with Sentry. Analytics with Vercel Analytics or Plausible. Performance monitoring. Uptime monitoring. User feedback widget."</p><h3>Phase 8: Launch Preparation</h3><h4>Create Landing Page</h4><p>Prompt: "Build a landing page with: Hero section with clear value proposition. Features section highlighting key benefits. Pricing table with three tiers. Testimonials section (can add later). FAQ section. CTA buttons leading to signup."</p><h4>Write Documentation</h4><p>Prompt: "Create user documentation: Getting started guide. Feature tutorials. FAQ. Troubleshooting common issues. API documentation (if applicable)."</p><h4>Legal Pages</h4><p>Prompt: "Generate templates for: Privacy Policy. Terms of Service. Cookie Policy. Refund Policy. Customize these with a lawyer before launch."</p><h3>Post-Launch: Iteration and Growth</h3><h4>Gather Feedback</h4><p>Add feedback mechanisms: In-app feedback widget. User surveys. Analytics to see feature usage. Monitor support requests.</p><h4>Iterate Based on Data</h4><p>Prompt: "Based on user feedback that [describe feedback], how should we improve [feature]?"</p><h4>Add Features Strategically</h4><p>Don''t build everything at once. Prioritize based on: User requests. Usage data. Business impact. Development effort.</p><h3>Common SaaS Challenges and Solutions</h3><p><strong>Challenge:</strong> Users aren''t converting to paid plans.<br><strong>Solution:</strong> Analyze where they drop off. Improve onboarding. Adjust pricing or features. Add social proof.</p><p><strong>Challenge:</strong> Performance degrades with more users.<br><strong>Solution:</strong> Optimize database queries. Add caching. Consider CDN. Scale infrastructure.</p><p><strong>Challenge:</strong> Support requests overwhelming.<br><strong>Solution:</strong> Improve documentation. Add in-app help. Create FAQ. Consider chatbot for common questions.</p><h3>Key Takeaways</h3><ul><li>Start with a <strong>clear MVP</strong> - core features only</li><li>Choose a <strong>modern, AI-friendly tech stack</strong> (Next.js, Supabase, Vercel)</li><li>Build <strong>iteratively</strong>: foundation ‚Üí core features ‚Üí polish ‚Üí billing</li><li>Use AI for <strong>every phase</strong>: planning, development, testing, deployment</li><li><strong>Test thoroughly</strong> before launch: functionality, edge cases, performance</li><li>Launch quickly and <strong>iterate based on feedback</strong></li><li>Focus on <strong>user value</strong>, not feature count</li></ul><p>In the next lesson, we''ll examine a real case study: building this LMS platform you''re using right now.</p></div>'
